We reiterated the audit recommendation that the LCE instruct the City Accountant to designate a personnel who shall be responsible in monitoring cash advances and do the following tasks:
inform and remind accountable officers of the due dates for liquidation of their cash advances;
determine the whereabouts and status of retired/resigned accountable officers with unliquidated cash advance;
prepare and serve demand letters to every accountable officer located;
search for the initial disbursement vouchers granting the cash advances to accountable officers;
gather evidences to support request for write-off of unliquidated cash advances (death certificate, clearance from money and property accountability, previous demand letters issued)
recommend actions to be undertaken through the preparation of a Status Report (request for write-off, endorse the case to the City Legal Office for appropriate legal action); and
coordinate with the Auditor for purposes of endorsing the case to the Civil Service Commission and the Ombudsman for further legal proceedings.
The City Accountant averred that he already sent demand letters to the accountable officers in February 2017 and that he instructed the accounting staff assigned in the recording of cash advances to monitor the liquidations or settlements by the accountable officers.

We reiterated the recommendation that the LCE create an inventory team and instruct the same to conduct a complete inventory taking of PPEs and Inventories as recommended in the CY 2015 AAR; and to prepare and submit RPCPPE.
